      <li>However, many Brits felt being an EU member made them worse off and felt it would be better to leave than remain.</li>
      <li>This was particularly following mass immigration from conflicts zones in Arab regions to Europe, raising security concerns among people and nationalism among conservatives.</li>
    </ul>
