#### Insight 3: Working conditions matter towards happiness

* Plotting economies with severance pay of 1 year tenure in a dot plot in figure 26, the purpose is to compare them against one another in terms of the severance pay they offer to employees

* Mexico has the highest severance pay at 1 year tenure at approximately 14.6, rounding to the nearest decimal place. This is followed by Lithuania and Greece.</li>

* Interestingly, Brazil does not have a universal severance pay across the country. In Sao Paulo, it is 1.7 while in Rio de Janeiro, it is 1.6.

* For France, the graph shows 2 values of 0.9 and 1.1 respectively. These 2 values are due to an increase in severance pay in 2019 from 0.9 to 1.1.

